vibe-engineer commands:
  help — List the v0.1 deterministic CLI primitives.
  version — Report package version.
  create — Create a new vibe-engineer starter project with a selected pi, Claude Code, or Codex agentic harness and DL-17 bootstrap context.
  import — Import an existing project into vibe-engineer management with a selected pi, Claude Code, or Codex agentic harness and DL-17 bootstrap context.
  doctor — Inspect read-only vibe-engineer project health through config-backed checks.
  config — Inspect or validate vibe-engineer configuration through the public config provider.
  verify — Run an approved Implementation Plan through the verification runner and emit CLI result evidence.
  security — Run fail-closed security and safety policy gates through @vibe-engineer/security.
  schematic — Plan, dry-run, or apply a manifest-driven schematic.
